- The task assumes that the input data is of high quality and has been properly preprocessed.
- The task requires the assistant to consider the nuances and variations in the ECG and echocardiogram data when making predictions.
- The task evaluation will consider the accuracy of the predicted likelihood of HCM, taking into account any limitations or biases in the model.
